<!---->  </span><span class=""> is sounding the alarm: wages between high- and low-income workers are drifting apart again after years of narrowing. The culprit? A wave of AI adoption that’s boosting productivity at the top while squeezing opportunities for workers in routine or entry-level roles.</span><!---->
