<!---->  </span><span class="">, a company that provides parental leave programs as an employee benefit to support parents, their managers, and their teams. She posted this picture of her and her "work leave hero" Pete Buttigieg. Mayor Pete is one of the only politicians I truly like. He listens first, he's articulate, and he leads with compassion and empathy rather than hate. You may remember that he took two months of parental leave after he and his partner adopted twins, and </span><span class=""><a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/health-wellness/2023/03/14/mike-pence-pete-buttigieg-mock-paternity-leave/11469353002/" target="_blank" data-tracking-control-name="article-ssr-frontend-pulse_little-text-block" data-tracking-will-navigate="" data-test-link="">was mocked by former Vice President Mike Pence<!----></a></span><span class=""> among others. Can we just let dads take time off to celebrate life? I have two girls, an 8 year old and a 4 year old. For my first, I think I got about 2 weeks which went by in a blur. For my second, my company updated their policy to give new dads a month off. I not only got to spend the time with her, but I got to support my wife and my other daughter as they adjusted to the new normal. Too often, fathers are praised for being workaholics and always putting work first family second. Work will come and go, but you will never get the time back with your kids. Let's normalize spending time with them. </span><!---->
