<!---->  </span><span class=""> conference multiple times and he is keynoting the conference again this year. I first got to interview him in 2017 in Phoenix while I was running the Workhuman Radio podcast. He's a unique blend of being not only super smart, but actually caring about people. Three cheers to both Adam and Glassdoor. Read the full announcement </span><span class=""><a href="https://www.hr-brew.com/stories/2025/01/15/worklife-expert-adam-grant-to-join-glassdoor?mbcid=38209063.85962&mid=2968e78e9f10d166c75466dd3c9ae3c7&utm_campaign=hrb&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_source=morning_brew" target="_blank" data-tracking-control-name="article-ssr-frontend-pulse_little-text-block" data-tracking-will-navigate="" data-test-link="">here<!----></a></span><span class="">. </span><!---->
