<!---->  </span><span class=""> shared that "June saw $1.4 billion invested across 72 deals for a $20.3 million average deal size). It was the third consecutive month of $1 billion-plus investment months." It was the best month in 2 years. Are we finally coming out of the HR Tech stalemate? I hope so. I'd rather read about increased sales, innovation, and hiring than </span><span class=""><a href="https://www.bizjournals.com/boston/news/2024/07/03/ukg-cuts-14-of-its-workforce.amp.html" target="_blank" data-tracking-control-name="article-ssr-frontend-pulse_little-text-block" data-tracking-will-navigate="" data-test-link="">layoffs<!----></a></span><span class=""> and reduced budgets. </span><!---->
